WEBVTT

1
00:03:11.050 --> 00:03:12.320
You're sure?

2
00:03:16.560 --> 00:03:18.220
With his own eyes. Your Grace.

3
00:03:30.510 --> 00:03:32.060
Stay here. Tell no one.

4
00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:35.500
Help me dress.

5
00:03:50.890 --> 00:03:52.020
Who knows?

6
00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:57.160
My handmaiden. Talya.

7
00:03:58.570 --> 00:03:59.590
Some of the servants.

8
00:04:05.510 --> 00:04:09.380
I saw him last night before he...

9
00:04:14.680 --> 00:04:16.580
He told me

10
00:04:14.680 --> 00:04:16.580
he wished for Aegon to be king.

11
00:04:25.860 --> 00:04:26.890
It is the truth.

12
00:04:28.300 --> 00:04:29.590
Uttered with his own lips.

13
00:04:31.300 --> 00:04:33.860
His last words to me

14
00:04:31.300 --> 00:04:33.860
and I was the only one to hear it.

15
00:04:35.270 --> 00:04:36.240
And now he's dead.

16
00:05:07.940 --> 00:05:09.960
What is it that could not

17
00:05:07.940 --> 00:05:09.960
have waited an hour?

18
00:05:10.070 --> 00:05:11.000
Was Dorne invaded?

19
00:05:15.140 --> 00:05:16.270
The King is dead.

20
00:05:26.860 --> 00:05:28.950
We grieve for Viserys the Peaceful.

21
00:05:30.860 --> 00:05:31.830
Our sovereign.

22
00:05:34.460 --> 00:05:35.450
Our friend.

23
00:05:39.630 --> 00:05:41.630
But he has left us a gift.

24
00:05:45.010 --> 00:05:49.140
With his last breath. he impressed

25
00:05:45.010 --> 00:05:49.140
upon the Queen his final wish

26
00:05:49.210 --> 00:05:51.150
that his son. Aegon...

27
00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:56.710
should succeed him

28
00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:56.710
as Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

29
00:06:06.030 --> 00:06:08.290
Then we may proceed now

30
00:06:06.030 --> 00:06:08.290
with the full assurance

31
00:06:08.360 --> 00:06:10.160
of his blessing on our long-laid plans.

32
00:06:11.030 --> 00:06:11.970
Yes.

33
00:06:12.030 --> 00:06:14.400
There is much to be done.

34
00:06:12.030 --> 00:06:14.400
as we've previously discussed.

35
00:06:14.500 --> 00:06:16.800
Now. there are two among the captains

36
00:06:16.870 --> 00:06:19.500
of the City Watch

37
00:06:16.870 --> 00:06:19.500
that remain loyal to Daemon.

38
00:06:19.570 --> 00:06:20.840
Let us replace them.

39
00:06:20.910 --> 00:06:22.040
Lord Lannister.

40
00:06:22.140 --> 00:06:23.810
The Treasury is well in hand.

41
00:06:23.880 --> 00:06:25.710
The gold will be divided

42
00:06:23.880 --> 00:06:25.710
for safekeeping.

43
00:06:25.810 --> 00:06:28.840
Let ravens be sent to our allies.

44
00:06:25.810 --> 00:06:28.840
Riverrun and Highgarden.

45
00:06:28.920 --> 00:06:30.820
Am I to understand

46
00:06:28.920 --> 00:06:30.820
that members of the Small Council

47
00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:34.250
have been planning secretly

48
00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:34.250
to install my son without me?

49
00:06:34.590 --> 00:06:38.860
My queen. there was no need

50
00:06:34.590 --> 00:06:38.860
to sully you with darkling schemes.

51
00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:40.890
I will not have this.

52
00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:43.020
To hear that you are plotting

53
00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:46.540
to replace the King's chosen heir

54
00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:46.540
with an imposter!

55
00:06:46.600 --> 00:06:48.830
His firstborn son is hardly an imposter.

56
00:06:48.900 --> 00:06:50.840
Hundreds of lords and landed knights

57
00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:52.270
swore fealty to the Princess.

58
00:06:52.370 --> 00:06:54.370
That was some 20 years ago.

59
00:06:52.370 --> 00:06:54.370
Most of them now dead.

60
00:06:54.440 --> 00:06:55.670
You heard the Lord Hand.

61
00:06:55.740 --> 00:06:58.010
Plot or no. the King changed his mind.

62
00:06:59.050 --> 00:07:01.110
I am six-and-seventy years old.

63
00:07:01.780 --> 00:07:06.080
I have known Viserys longer

64
00:07:01.780 --> 00:07:06.080
than any who sit at this table.

65
00:07:06.190 --> 00:07:10.560
And I will not believe that he said this

66
00:07:06.190 --> 00:07:10.560
on his deathbed. alone.

67
00:07:10.630 --> 00:07:13.860
with only the boy's mother as a witness.

68
00:07:14.930 --> 00:07:16.900
- This is seizure!

69
00:07:16.970 --> 00:07:19.460
It is theft! It is treason!

70
00:07:19.570 --> 00:07:22.540
- At the least. it is--

71
00:07:19.570 --> 00:07:22.540
- Mind your tongue. Lyman.

72
00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:25.230
The King was well last night...

73
00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:27.070
by all accounts.

74
00:07:29.610 --> 00:07:33.950
Which of you here can swear

75
00:07:29.610 --> 00:07:33.950
that he died of his own accord?

76
00:07:34.050 --> 00:07:37.780
Which of us are you accusing

77
00:07:34.050 --> 00:07:37.780
of regicide. Lord Beesbury?

78
00:07:37.890 --> 00:07:42.260
Whether it was one of you.

79
00:07:37.890 --> 00:07:42.260
or all of you. I care not.

80
00:07:42.320 --> 00:07:44.120
- I will have no part--

81
00:07:42.320 --> 00:07:44.120
- Sit down!

82
00:07:44.230 --> 00:07:45.660
Ser Criston.

83
00:07:58.140 --> 00:08:01.270
Throw down your sword

84
00:07:58.140 --> 00:08:01.270
and remove your cloak. Ser Criston.

85
00:08:04.250 --> 00:08:06.240
I am your Lord Commander. Ser Criston.

86
00:08:07.080 --> 00:08:08.570
Cast down your sword.

87
00:08:08.650 --> 00:08:11.250
I will not suffer insults

88
00:08:08.650 --> 00:08:11.250
to Her Grace the Queen.

89
00:08:11.320 --> 00:08:14.480
There was no insult to me. Ser Criston.

90
00:08:11.320 --> 00:08:14.480
Put aside your blade.

91
00:08:22.700 --> 00:08:25.460
- Has it come to this?

92
00:08:22.700 --> 00:08:25.460
- Lord Commander. enough.

93
00:08:29.170 --> 00:08:32.000
- Let us have Lord Beesbury removed.

94
00:08:29.170 --> 00:08:32.000
No.

95
00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:36.970
The door remains shut

96
00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:36.970
until we finish our business.

97
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:55.860
Storm's End is of concern.

98
00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:59.130
We may not assume

99
00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:59.130
the loyalty of Lord Borros.

100
00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:01.830
But he has four daughters.

101
00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:01.830
all of them unmarried.

102
00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:04.070
- The right proposal--

103
00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:04.070
- What of Rhaenyra?

104
00:09:05.140 --> 00:09:08.840
The former heir cannot.

105
00:09:05.140 --> 00:09:08.840
of course. be allowed to remain free

106
00:09:08.910 --> 00:09:11.070
and draw support to her claim.

107
00:09:12.980 --> 00:09:14.010
You mean to imprison her.

108
00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:16.640
She and her family

109
00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:16.640
will be given the opportunity

110
00:09:16.720 --> 00:09:19.090
to publicly swear obeisance

111
00:09:19.190 --> 00:09:20.180
- to the new King.

112
00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:22.250
She will never bend the knee.

113
00:09:23.060 --> 00:09:24.650
Nor will Daemon. which you know.

114
00:09:30.370 --> 00:09:31.390
You plan to kill them.

115
00:09:37.070 --> 00:09:38.730
And all here accede to this.

116
00:09:38.840 --> 00:09:41.040
Your father is correct.

117
00:09:38.840 --> 00:09:41.040
Your Grace.

118
00:09:41.110 --> 00:09:44.600
A living challenger

119
00:09:41.110 --> 00:09:44.600
invites battle and bloodshed.

120
00:09:44.710 --> 00:09:46.770
It is unsavory. yes.

121
00:09:47.850 --> 00:09:51.220
But a sacrifice we must make

122
00:09:47.850 --> 00:09:51.220
to secure Aegon's succession.

123
00:09:51.290 --> 00:09:53.380
And then there is Daemon to consider.

124
00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:54.860
The King wouldn't wish

125
00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:54.860
for any unsavory--

126
00:09:54.920 --> 00:09:57.420
But the King did not wish

127
00:09:54.920 --> 00:09:57.420
for the murder of his daughter!

128
00:09:58.960 --> 00:10:00.790
He loved her.

129
00:09:58.960 --> 00:10:00.790
I will not have you deny this.

130
00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:02.300
- And yet--

131
00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:02.300
- One more word

132
00:10:02.400 --> 00:10:04.800
and I will have you removed

133
00:10:02.400 --> 00:10:04.800
from this chamber and sent to the Wall!

134
00:10:15.610 --> 00:10:17.370
What do you suggest. Your Grace?

135
00:10:21.750 --> 00:10:23.120
Time is of the essence.

136
00:10:33.660 --> 00:10:35.150
Lord Commander Westerling.

137
00:10:37.270 --> 00:10:38.960
take your knights to Dragonstone.

138
00:10:39.070 --> 00:10:40.400
Be quick and be clean.

139
00:10:54.980 --> 00:10:57.180
I am Lord Commander of the Kingsguard.

140
00:11:00.690 --> 00:11:02.950
I recognize no authority but the King's.

141
00:11:04.760 --> 00:11:06.250
And until there is one...

142
00:11:08.960 --> 00:11:10.020
I have no place here.

143
00:11:22.840 --> 00:11:24.680
It is our fate. I think.

144
00:11:24.780 --> 00:11:27.010
to crave always

145
00:11:24.780 --> 00:11:27.010
what is given to another.

146
00:11:27.850 --> 00:11:31.650
If one possesses a thing.

147
00:11:27.850 --> 00:11:31.650
the other will take it away.

148
00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:33.190
Yes. Princess.

149
00:11:37.060 --> 00:11:38.290
Where is Aegon?

150
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:42.550
Not here.

151
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:44.160
He's not in his rooms.

152
00:11:51.540 --> 00:11:52.530
Father...

153
00:12:02.320 --> 00:12:03.380
What's happened?

154
00:12:19.000 --> 00:12:21.830
- Your father--

155
00:12:19.000 --> 00:12:21.830
- There is a beast beneath the boards.

156
00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:23.930
Tsk. Oh. my dearest love.

157
00:12:45.560 --> 00:12:46.690
Ser Erryk.

158
00:12:50.770 --> 00:12:51.760
Where's the Prince?

159
00:12:52.470 --> 00:12:55.270
Forgive me. Lord Hand. I do not know.

160
00:12:55.370 --> 00:12:56.960
But you're sworn to protect him.

161
00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:59.640
He exploits his authority

162
00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:59.640
to order me away.

163
00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:01.210
and then he evades me. my lord.

164
00:13:05.780 --> 00:13:07.720
I believe he may have

165
00:13:05.780 --> 00:13:07.720
left the Keep secretly.

166
00:13:08.950 --> 00:13:09.820
gone into the city.

167
00:13:10.590 --> 00:13:11.580
Find him.

168
00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:18.720
Take no one else but your brother.

169
00:13:19.790 --> 00:13:21.390
And remove your white cloaks.

170
00:13:21.460 --> 00:13:23.660
None can know who you are

171
00:13:21.460 --> 00:13:23.660
or what you seek...

172
00:13:24.400 --> 00:13:25.560
including the Queen.

173
00:13:26.670 --> 00:13:27.600
My lord.

174
00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.800
Bring him to me.

175
00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.800
and me alone. Ser Erryk.

176
00:13:50.790 --> 00:13:52.590
What is the meaning of this?

177
00:14:13.310 --> 00:14:14.940
Guard. Guard!

178
00:14:29.500 --> 00:14:32.370
Prince Aegon's not to be found

179
00:14:29.500 --> 00:14:32.370
within the castle walls. Your Grace.

180
00:14:32.470 --> 00:14:34.530
Your father has sent

181
00:14:32.470 --> 00:14:34.530
Ser Erryk into the city to find him.

182
00:14:37.410 --> 00:14:39.670
Ser Erryk knows Aegon.

183
00:14:37.410 --> 00:14:39.670
He has the advantage.

184
00:14:47.250 --> 00:14:51.020
I trust again to you. Ser Criston.

185
00:14:47.250 --> 00:14:51.020
and to your loyalty.

186
00:14:52.050 --> 00:14:54.320
Aegon must be found.

187
00:14:52.050 --> 00:14:54.320
and he must be brought to me.

188
00:14:55.560 --> 00:14:57.820
The very fate of the Seven Kingdoms

189
00:14:55.560 --> 00:14:57.820
depends on it.

190
00:14:59.830 --> 00:15:02.490
Everything you feel for me

191
00:14:59.830 --> 00:15:02.490
as your queen.

192
00:15:05.230 --> 00:15:06.360
I will not fail you.

193
00:15:07.570 --> 00:15:08.700
I'll come with you.

194
00:15:09.570 --> 00:15:12.010
That would not be my desire. Aemond.

195
00:15:12.940 --> 00:15:14.570
If anything has happened--

196
00:15:14.680 --> 00:15:16.840
Cole needs me. Mother.

197
00:15:16.910 --> 00:15:19.750
Ser Erryk isn't the only one

198
00:15:16.910 --> 00:15:19.750
who knows Aegon's doings.

199
00:15:46.570 --> 00:15:48.240
Aegon brought me

200
00:15:46.570 --> 00:15:48.240
to the Street of Silk

201
00:15:48.310 --> 00:15:49.780
on my 13th name day.

202
00:15:50.780 --> 00:15:56.410
It was his duty as my brother. he said.

203
00:15:50.780 --> 00:15:56.410
to ensure I was as educated as he was.

204
00:16:00.420 --> 00:16:03.720
At least that's what

205
00:16:00.420 --> 00:16:03.720
I understood him to mean.

206
00:16:06.160 --> 00:16:07.060
I don't follow.

207
00:16:08.230 --> 00:16:09.750
He said. "Time to get it wet."

208
00:16:10.770 --> 00:16:14.460
Every woman is an image of the Mother.

209
00:16:10.770 --> 00:16:14.460
to be spoken of with reverence.

210
00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:28.110
Sometime last night.

211
00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:28.110
we misplaced our drinking companion.

212
00:16:28.180 --> 00:16:31.580
Knowing that he has been. in the past.

213
00:16:28.180 --> 00:16:31.580
a patron of your fine establishment.

214
00:16:31.650 --> 00:16:33.920
we thought to inquire here

215
00:16:31.650 --> 00:16:33.920
as to his whereabouts.

216
00:16:34.590 --> 00:16:35.450
And describe him.

217
00:16:36.760 --> 00:16:38.280
That is a delicate matter.

218
00:16:39.860 --> 00:16:42.920
You see. the man we seek

219
00:16:39.860 --> 00:16:42.920
is the young Prince Aegon.

220
00:16:43.870 --> 00:16:46.160
I may trust. I hope.

221
00:16:43.870 --> 00:16:46.160
in the discretion of your trade.

222
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:49.200
The Prince is not here.

223
00:16:50.810 --> 00:16:53.930
Has he been here? Earlier. perhaps?

224
00:16:54.840 --> 00:16:57.540
Quite a bit earlier. Years ago. in fact.

225
00:16:57.650 --> 00:16:58.700
But more recently?

226
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:02.980
He does not frequent

227
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:02.980
the Street of Silk.

228
00:17:03.950 --> 00:17:05.890
His tastes are known to be...

229
00:17:07.390 --> 00:17:08.860
less discriminating.

230
00:17:10.060 --> 00:17:11.220
Meaning what?

231
00:17:12.730 --> 00:17:17.320
I wish you luck. good Ser.

232
00:17:12.730 --> 00:17:17.320
And my best to your friend.

233
00:17:24.470 --> 00:17:25.530
How you've grown.

234
00:17:28.980 --> 00:17:29.880
Hmm.

235
00:17:33.550 --> 00:17:35.310
Viserys amended his wishes.

236
00:17:35.880 --> 00:17:37.180
It's as simple as that.

237
00:17:39.990 --> 00:17:42.010
You once swore your banners to Rhaenyra.

238
00:17:42.090 --> 00:17:46.750
You must now

239
00:17:42.090 --> 00:17:46.750
pledge them to the future king.

240
00:17:53.600 --> 00:17:57.400
I must confer first

241
00:17:53.600 --> 00:17:57.400
with my house on this matter.

242
00:17:59.010 --> 00:18:02.240
You'll not leave this room

243
00:17:59.010 --> 00:18:02.240
without declaring your intention.

244
00:18:12.720 --> 00:18:14.250
I am no oath breaker.

245
00:18:17.590 --> 00:18:19.390
I will not bend the knee.

246
00:18:27.540 --> 00:18:28.630
Anyone else?

247
00:18:41.080 --> 00:18:45.540
House Fell keeps its sworn oath

248
00:18:41.080 --> 00:18:45.540
to the Princess.

249
00:18:49.120 --> 00:18:50.150
Very well.

250
00:19:10.680 --> 00:19:11.840
Long live the King.

251
00:19:11.950 --> 00:19:13.640
Long live the King.

252
00:19:45.850 --> 00:19:48.010
It seems you were mistaken

253
00:19:45.850 --> 00:19:48.010
as to Aegon's habits.

254
00:19:48.720 --> 00:19:52.880
He could be in the hands

255
00:19:48.720 --> 00:19:52.880
of mercenaries. on a ship to Yi Ti.

256
00:19:53.950 --> 00:19:54.850
He could be dead.

257
00:19:55.790 --> 00:19:58.390
Let us hope. for your mother's sake.

258
00:19:55.790 --> 00:19:58.390
that is not the case.

259
00:20:14.380 --> 00:20:15.670
Let's have a look.

260
00:20:15.740 --> 00:20:18.470
- Go on.

261
00:20:15.740 --> 00:20:18.470
Come here. Come here!

262
00:20:18.550 --> 00:20:19.510
Get in there. you little--

263
00:20:27.660 --> 00:20:29.020
Yeah!

264
00:20:30.020 --> 00:20:31.390
Come on!

265
00:20:39.170 --> 00:20:40.230
How old are they?

266
00:20:42.170 --> 00:20:43.690
About ten years. I should say.

267
00:20:44.840 --> 00:20:47.070
They have them grow their nails

268
00:20:44.840 --> 00:20:47.070
and file the teeth.

269
00:20:48.240 --> 00:20:49.440
Makes them more formidable.

270
00:20:50.540 --> 00:20:51.740
Come on!

271
00:20:51.850 --> 00:20:53.910
Prince Aegon spends many

272
00:20:51.850 --> 00:20:53.910
a night in this place.

273
00:20:54.680 --> 00:20:57.120
- Do you see now what he is?

274
00:20:57.220 --> 00:20:58.410
You've not seen everything.

275
00:21:06.630 --> 00:21:09.390
- Aegon's?

276
00:21:06.630 --> 00:21:09.390
- One of many. I'd wager.

277
00:21:27.410 --> 00:21:30.910
Here I am. trawling the city.

278
00:21:27.410 --> 00:21:30.910
ever the good soldier

279
00:21:30.990 --> 00:21:34.150
in search of a wastrel who's never taken

280
00:21:30.990 --> 00:21:34.150
half an interest in his birthright.

281
00:21:36.090 --> 00:21:39.080
'Tis I the younger brother

282
00:21:36.090 --> 00:21:39.080
who studies history and philosophy.

283
00:21:39.160 --> 00:21:40.630
it is I who trains with the sword.

284
00:21:40.730 --> 00:21:42.630
who rides

285
00:21:40.730 --> 00:21:42.630
the largest dragon in the world.

286
00:21:42.730 --> 00:21:43.960
It is I who should be--

287
00:21:48.500 --> 00:21:51.470
I know what it is to toil

288
00:21:48.500 --> 00:21:51.470
for what others are freely given.

289
00:21:51.570 --> 00:21:52.730
Mmm.

290
00:21:55.080 --> 00:21:56.480
And we can't find him. Cole.

291
00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:00.010
You are a decent man

292
00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:00.010
with no taste for depravity.

293
00:22:00.650 --> 00:22:01.810
His secrets are his own.

294
00:22:02.680 --> 00:22:03.950
And he's welcome to them.

295
00:22:04.020 --> 00:22:05.680
I'm next in line to the throne.

296
00:22:07.090 --> 00:22:08.580
Should they come looking for me.

297
00:22:09.460 --> 00:22:10.790
I intend to be found.

298
00:22:20.840 --> 00:22:22.360
Something must be done.

299
00:22:22.470 --> 00:22:24.030
Aegon is unfit to rule.

300
00:22:24.140 --> 00:22:26.200
You tolerated

301
00:22:24.140 --> 00:22:26.200
the Prince's proclivities for years.

302
00:22:26.310 --> 00:22:27.970
Because it was my sworn duty. Arryk.

303
00:22:28.040 --> 00:22:29.440
It's for the Hand to find wisdom.

304
00:22:30.040 --> 00:22:32.170
We swore an oath of service until death.

305
00:22:32.280 --> 00:22:33.680
A moment of your time. m'lords.

306
00:22:35.480 --> 00:22:37.310
You'll find no buyers

307
00:22:35.480 --> 00:22:37.310
for your wares here.

308
00:22:41.390 --> 00:22:42.880
I can take you to Prince Aegon.

309
00:22:45.230 --> 00:22:47.320
Rather. I am sent by one

310
00:22:45.230 --> 00:22:47.320
who knows where he is.

311
00:22:48.300 --> 00:22:50.230
Who'll tell you. for a price.

312
00:22:51.830 --> 00:22:54.860
Deliver him.

313
00:22:51.830 --> 00:22:54.860
and we'll consider your price.

314
00:22:55.540 --> 00:22:58.030
My mistress will not

315
00:22:55.540 --> 00:22:58.030
treat with the servants of the Keep.

316
00:22:59.510 --> 00:23:00.870
exalted though they may be.

317
00:23:02.480 --> 00:23:04.740
She'll trust this

318
00:23:02.480 --> 00:23:04.740
to the Hand of the King only.

319
00:23:04.850 --> 00:23:05.810
Impossible.

320
00:23:07.720 --> 00:23:10.580
I think he will wish to hear

321
00:23:07.720 --> 00:23:10.580
what the White Worm can tell him.

322
00:23:26.400 --> 00:23:28.890
Halt! Hold the gate!

323
00:23:31.840 --> 00:23:32.930
Let go of me!

324
00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:34.840
He was fleeing from the gate.

325
00:23:34.910 --> 00:23:35.900
Do you know who I am?

326
00:23:36.010 --> 00:23:38.070
A warning for the Princess.

327
00:23:36.010 --> 00:23:38.070
I'd wager.

328
00:23:40.510 --> 00:23:41.610
What say you?

329
00:23:42.920 --> 00:23:45.110
The Lord Confessor presumes.

330
00:23:47.550 --> 00:23:49.610
I have no love for the Princess.

331
00:23:50.020 --> 00:23:52.430
And where were you going then

332
00:23:50.020 --> 00:23:52.430
with such urgency?

333
00:23:59.130 --> 00:24:01.130
Let the King's Justice take him.

334
00:24:05.770 --> 00:24:07.210
Let go of me!

335
00:24:07.270 --> 00:24:09.770
- No! This is not right!

336
00:24:07.270 --> 00:24:09.770
- You did well. Lord Larys.

337
00:24:10.380 --> 00:24:13.070
I will--

338
00:24:10.380 --> 00:24:13.070
- Only my duty. my lord Hand.

339
00:24:13.150 --> 00:24:14.480
Who do you think you are?

340
00:24:14.580 --> 00:24:16.480
You've spent many hours

341
00:24:14.580 --> 00:24:16.480
with the Queen of late.

342
00:24:23.590 --> 00:24:28.050
There's no reason those hours could not.

343
00:24:23.590 --> 00:24:28.050
in the end. benefit you.

344
00:25:58.590 --> 00:26:00.850
I will do you the considerable

345
00:25:58.590 --> 00:26:00.850
courtesy of assuming

346
00:26:00.920 --> 00:26:04.480
there is a good reason for the outrage

347
00:26:00.920 --> 00:26:04.480
of my treatment here this morning.

348
00:26:06.390 --> 00:26:08.730
My sincerest regrets

349
00:26:06.390 --> 00:26:08.730
for the lack of ceremony.

350
00:26:12.070 --> 00:26:13.160
The King.

351
00:26:19.240 --> 00:26:21.040
And you are usurping the throne.

352
00:26:21.110 --> 00:26:23.010
It was my husband's dying wish.

353
00:26:23.110 --> 00:26:24.840
Believe it or no.

354
00:26:24.910 --> 00:26:26.380
it is of no consequence.

355
00:26:26.950 --> 00:26:28.210
Aegon will be king.

356
00:26:31.850 --> 00:26:33.550
I came here to ask your support.

357
00:26:34.590 --> 00:26:36.780
Well. I must credit you

358
00:26:34.590 --> 00:26:36.780
for your boldness.

359
00:26:38.090 --> 00:26:41.360
House Velaryon has long allied itself

360
00:26:38.090 --> 00:26:41.360
with the Princess Rhaenyra

361
00:26:41.430 --> 00:26:42.920
and what has it gained you?

362
00:26:44.700 --> 00:26:47.600
Your daughter dead. alone in Pentos.

363
00:26:48.870 --> 00:26:50.740
Your son cuckolded.

364
00:26:50.800 --> 00:26:52.530
Rhaenyra's heirs are none of yours.

365
00:26:54.610 --> 00:26:58.550
It is your husband

366
00:26:54.610 --> 00:26:58.550
who grasps so heedlessly for the throne.

367
00:26:59.480 --> 00:27:01.110
And even he has abandoned you.

368
00:27:01.220 --> 00:27:03.910
Gone these six long years

369
00:27:01.220 --> 00:27:03.910
to fight a desperate battle.

370
00:27:03.980 --> 00:27:06.750
returning grievously.

371
00:27:03.980 --> 00:27:06.750
if not mortally. wounded.

372
00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:09.880
leaving the Lady of Driftmark

373
00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:09.880
to chart her course alone.

374
00:27:12.630 --> 00:27:15.390
The word of my house is not fickle.

375
00:27:17.600 --> 00:27:18.500
No.

376
00:27:18.600 --> 00:27:20.590
But. dear cousin.

377
00:27:22.470 --> 00:27:26.670
you more than any soul alive

378
00:27:22.470 --> 00:27:26.670
understand what I say now.

379
00:27:26.770 --> 00:27:30.640
Princess Rhaenys. I loved my husband.

380
00:27:26.770 --> 00:27:30.640
but I will speak the truth we both know.

381
00:27:32.180 --> 00:27:33.410
You should've been queen.

382
00:27:36.280 --> 00:27:38.450
I little thought to hear

383
00:27:36.280 --> 00:27:38.450
those words from you.

384
00:27:38.520 --> 00:27:41.350
The Iron Throne was yours

385
00:27:38.520 --> 00:27:41.350
by blood and by temperament.

386
00:27:41.460 --> 00:27:44.020
Viserys would've lived

387
00:27:41.460 --> 00:27:44.020
his days a country lord.

388
00:27:44.120 --> 00:27:48.080
content to hunt and study his histories.

389
00:27:44.120 --> 00:27:48.080
but here we are.

390
00:27:50.830 --> 00:27:54.130
We do not rule.

391
00:27:50.830 --> 00:27:54.130
but we may guide the men that do.

392
00:27:55.300 --> 00:27:56.200
Gently.

393
00:27:56.970 --> 00:28:00.600
Away from violence and sure destruction

394
00:27:56.970 --> 00:28:00.600
and instead toward peace.

395
00:28:02.340 --> 00:28:04.470
Is it in the name of peace

396
00:28:02.340 --> 00:28:04.470
that you've imprisoned me?

397
00:28:05.380 --> 00:28:06.610
And what of my dragon?

398
00:28:06.680 --> 00:28:07.700
If we are overmatched.

399
00:28:07.810 --> 00:28:10.110
Rhaenyra will be tempted to strike us.

400
00:28:07.810 --> 00:28:10.110
and war will ensue.

401
00:28:11.990 --> 00:28:14.820
Without your dragon.

402
00:28:11.990 --> 00:28:14.820
she may be persuaded to negotiate.

403
00:28:17.620 --> 00:28:19.820
If it's Driftmark you want.

404
00:28:17.620 --> 00:28:19.820
you shall have it

405
00:28:20.660 --> 00:28:23.650
for you and your granddaughters

406
00:28:20.660 --> 00:28:23.650
to pass on as you see fit.

407
00:28:28.970 --> 00:28:31.000
You are wiser than I believed you to be.

408
00:28:34.880 --> 00:28:36.310
Alicent Hightower.

409
00:28:37.140 --> 00:28:40.380
A true queen counts

410
00:28:37.140 --> 00:28:40.380
the cost to her people.

411
00:28:42.050 --> 00:28:45.320
And yet you toil still

412
00:28:42.050 --> 00:28:45.320
in service to men.

413
00:28:45.390 --> 00:28:48.510
Your father. your husband. your son.

414
00:28:50.590 --> 00:28:52.180
You desire not to be free.

415
00:28:52.260 --> 00:28:55.250
but to make a window

416
00:28:52.260 --> 00:28:55.250
in the wall of your prison.

417
00:28:56.530 --> 00:29:01.660
Have you never imagined yourself

418
00:28:56.530 --> 00:29:01.660
on the Iron Throne?

419
00:29:14.110 --> 00:29:15.740
I'll leave you with your thoughts.

420
00:29:18.890 --> 00:29:20.550
Ring the bell when you have an answer.

421
00:29:45.310 --> 00:29:46.250
My prince.

422
00:29:56.720 --> 00:30:00.660
You yourself are the mysterious

423
00:29:56.720 --> 00:30:00.660
White Worm. I take it.

424
00:30:02.230 --> 00:30:05.390
Or are you simply a further peel

425
00:30:02.230 --> 00:30:05.390
in this stinking onion?

426
00:30:08.000 --> 00:30:10.990
My condolences

427
00:30:08.000 --> 00:30:10.990
on the passing of your king.

428
00:30:25.990 --> 00:30:27.450
Where is Prince Aegon?

429
00:30:28.020 --> 00:30:33.590
I thought. the Prince is in Flea Bottom

430
00:30:28.020 --> 00:30:33.590
where no one is to be trusted.

431
00:30:34.160 --> 00:30:39.360
I'd best secrete him somewhere safe

432
00:30:34.160 --> 00:30:39.360
in case they come looking for him.

433
00:30:39.470 --> 00:30:40.800
Where's the Prince?

434
00:30:41.800 --> 00:30:43.600
He is safely tucked away.

435
00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:50.670
I want an end to the savage use

436
00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:50.670
of children in Flea Bottom.

437
00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:54.140
They are forced to fight. and worse.

438
00:30:54.780 --> 00:30:58.680
your gold cloaks take

439
00:30:54.780 --> 00:30:58.680
the bribes given them to look away.

440
00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:05.980
An obscenity either tolerated

441
00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:05.980
or ignored by the Crown.

442
00:31:07.790 --> 00:31:09.230
I'll look into it.

443
00:31:09.800 --> 00:31:10.790
You have my word.

444
00:31:16.640 --> 00:31:18.300
When your plots ripen

445
00:31:18.370 --> 00:31:21.540
and you install your grandson

446
00:31:18.370 --> 00:31:21.540
on the throne.

447
00:31:22.640 --> 00:31:25.700
remember it was me who put him there.

448
00:31:25.810 --> 00:31:30.010
I could have killed him

449
00:31:25.810 --> 00:31:30.010
as easily as a wasp on fruit.

450
00:31:30.350 --> 00:31:35.080
There is no power

451
00:31:30.350 --> 00:31:35.080
but what the people allow you to take.

452
00:31:37.720 --> 00:31:38.920
I will remember.

453
00:32:04.050 --> 00:32:04.950
Listen.

454
00:32:14.190 --> 00:32:15.420
No... No!

455
00:32:16.400 --> 00:32:17.260
No!

456
00:32:26.140 --> 00:32:27.570
Where is the White Worm?

457
00:32:28.410 --> 00:32:29.740
She sold you for a price.

458
00:32:29.810 --> 00:32:31.240
And why have you paid it?

459
00:32:33.250 --> 00:32:34.370
I want my mother.

460
00:32:36.050 --> 00:32:38.710
Your grandfather. the Hand.

461
00:32:36.050 --> 00:32:38.710
will meet you outside the city walls.

462
00:32:47.660 --> 00:32:50.060
You flee what other men

463
00:32:47.660 --> 00:32:50.060
die seeking. Aegon.

464
00:33:06.610 --> 00:33:08.080
I do regret this. friend.

465
00:33:38.950 --> 00:33:41.510
No! Stop! No.

466
00:33:46.120 --> 00:33:48.990
- I was hoping you disappeared.

467
00:33:46.120 --> 00:33:48.990
- Is our father truly dead?

468
00:33:49.060 --> 00:33:52.550
- Yes and they're going to make you king.

469
00:33:54.030 --> 00:33:56.360
No!

470
00:33:54.030 --> 00:33:56.360
Are you going to help me?

471
00:33:59.130 --> 00:34:01.360
No! Let me go!

472
00:34:01.470 --> 00:34:02.530
Where's your brother. huh?

473
00:34:03.000 --> 00:34:04.030
Huh?

474
00:34:04.640 --> 00:34:05.800
Let me go!

475
00:34:06.370 --> 00:34:07.400
Brother!

476
00:34:14.710 --> 00:34:15.740
Let me go!

477
00:34:17.420 --> 00:34:18.980
I have no wish to rule!

478
00:34:19.050 --> 00:34:21.680
No taste for duty! I'm not suited.

479
00:34:21.760 --> 00:34:23.090
You'll get no argument from me.

480
00:34:24.160 --> 00:34:27.990
You let me go. I will find a ship

481
00:34:24.160 --> 00:34:27.990
and sail away. never to be found.

482
00:34:32.170 --> 00:34:33.260
The Queen awaits.

483
00:35:04.560 --> 00:35:05.460
Well played.

484
00:35:06.400 --> 00:35:07.530
None of this is a game.

485
00:35:07.600 --> 00:35:09.700
And yet you treat it as one.

486
00:35:11.240 --> 00:35:16.300
A charming contest.

487
00:35:11.240 --> 00:35:16.300
the prize. a pouch of silver.

488
00:35:21.750 --> 00:35:23.770
We have relied on one another

489
00:35:21.750 --> 00:35:23.770
these many years.

490
00:35:23.880 --> 00:35:27.320
And now it is the good of the family

491
00:35:23.880 --> 00:35:27.320
that we both desire.

492
00:35:28.660 --> 00:35:31.630
Whatever our differences.

493
00:35:28.660 --> 00:35:31.630
our hearts remain as one.

494
00:35:33.960 --> 00:35:35.330
Our hearts were never one.

495
00:35:36.000 --> 00:35:36.830
I see that now.

496
00:35:37.630 --> 00:35:40.290
Rather. I have been a piece

497
00:35:37.630 --> 00:35:40.290
that you moved about the board.

498
00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:44.270
If that is true. then I made you

499
00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:44.270
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

500
00:35:45.840 --> 00:35:48.070
Would you have

501
00:35:45.840 --> 00:35:48.070
desired it otherwise?

502
00:35:48.140 --> 00:35:49.130
How could I know?

503
00:35:50.240 --> 00:35:52.610
I wanted whatever you

504
00:35:50.240 --> 00:35:52.610
impressed upon me to want.

505
00:35:54.580 --> 00:35:55.840
And now the debt comes due.

506
00:35:57.320 --> 00:35:59.910
- A debt you were happy enough to pay.

507
00:35:57.320 --> 00:35:59.910
- A sacrifice.

508
00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:04.090
A sacrifice

509
00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:04.090
made for the stability of the realm.

510
00:36:04.990 --> 00:36:07.190
No king has ever lived

511
00:36:04.990 --> 00:36:07.190
that hasn't had to forfeit

512
00:36:07.290 --> 00:36:09.350
the lives of a few to protect the many.

513
00:36:09.460 --> 00:36:11.620
Though I understand your squeamishness.

514
00:36:11.700 --> 00:36:15.290
Reluctance to murder is not a weakness!

515
00:36:19.010 --> 00:36:19.940
I have Aegon.

516
00:36:20.770 --> 00:36:22.500
We'll proceed now as I see fit.

517
00:36:29.350 --> 00:36:31.510
We will send terms

518
00:36:29.350 --> 00:36:31.510
to Rhaenyra on Dragonstone.

519
00:36:32.550 --> 00:36:35.780
True terms. such that she

520
00:36:32.550 --> 00:36:35.780
may accept without shame.

521
00:36:35.860 --> 00:36:39.490
If she lives. her allies

522
00:36:35.860 --> 00:36:39.490
will mass behind her banners.

523
00:36:39.560 --> 00:36:40.990
looking for her return.

524
00:36:41.060 --> 00:36:42.190
Then she must not return.

525
00:36:43.400 --> 00:36:45.990
My husband would have desired

526
00:36:43.400 --> 00:36:45.990
this mercy be shown to his daughter.

527
00:36:46.070 --> 00:36:46.970
Your husband?

528
00:36:47.900 --> 00:36:50.700
Or you. his daughter's

529
00:36:47.900 --> 00:36:50.700
childhood companion?

530
00:36:55.240 --> 00:36:58.180
Criston Cole will be named

531
00:36:55.240 --> 00:36:58.180
Lord Commander of the Kingsguard.

532
00:36:59.850 --> 00:37:01.640
My son will be anointed

533
00:36:59.850 --> 00:37:01.640
tomorrow at dawn.

534
00:37:02.650 --> 00:37:04.740
The whole of King's Landing

535
00:37:02.650 --> 00:37:04.740
must witness his ascent.

536
00:37:06.090 --> 00:37:09.150
He will assume authority.

537
00:37:06.090 --> 00:37:09.150
There will be no more dithering.

538
00:37:09.820 --> 00:37:12.260
My son will take the crown

539
00:37:09.820 --> 00:37:12.260
of his namesake. the Conqueror.

540
00:37:12.360 --> 00:37:14.350
and carry Blackfyre. his sword.

541
00:37:14.430 --> 00:37:17.920
Let the people remember

542
00:37:14.430 --> 00:37:17.920
the ancient strength of House Targaryen.

543
00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:25.200
You look so much like your mother

544
00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:25.200
in certain lights.

545
00:37:36.520 --> 00:37:37.580
As you wish.

546
00:37:49.460 --> 00:37:50.450
Your Grace.

547
00:37:54.870 --> 00:37:56.800
The hour is late. Lord Larys.

548
00:37:58.470 --> 00:38:01.370
I've found out something

549
00:37:58.470 --> 00:38:01.370
that you should know.

550
00:38:13.950 --> 00:38:16.450
Have you asked yourself. I wonder.

551
00:38:17.320 --> 00:38:18.310
how it is...

552
00:38:19.630 --> 00:38:21.650
that your father. the Hand.

553
00:38:23.730 --> 00:38:25.320
found Aegon first?

554
00:38:58.670 --> 00:39:01.530
There is a web of spies

555
00:38:58.670 --> 00:39:01.530
at work in the Red Keep.

556
00:39:02.700 --> 00:39:06.760
Along its threads

557
00:39:02.700 --> 00:39:06.760
travels news of all our doings.

558
00:39:07.440 --> 00:39:11.610
Your father knows this.

559
00:39:07.440 --> 00:39:11.610
but has left it in place.

560
00:39:12.980 --> 00:39:16.610
More than once. it has proved

561
00:39:12.980 --> 00:39:16.610
advantageous to those willing to

562
00:39:18.280 --> 00:39:20.380
- feed the weaver.

563
00:39:21.720 --> 00:39:23.120
And this weaver watches me?

564
00:39:26.490 --> 00:39:27.520
Um...

565
00:39:48.550 --> 00:39:53.010
One of the little spiders

566
00:39:48.550 --> 00:39:53.010
is your lady-in-waiting.

567
00:39:55.020 --> 00:39:56.080
Talya?

568
00:39:56.190 --> 00:39:57.750
There are more like her.

569
00:39:57.860 --> 00:39:59.590
Even I do not know their number.

570
00:40:04.660 --> 00:40:07.690
There is one way

571
00:40:04.660 --> 00:40:07.690
to destroy his advantage.

572
00:40:08.900 --> 00:40:11.600
It must be taken out at the head.

573
00:40:13.710 --> 00:40:18.170
When the queen dies.

574
00:40:13.710 --> 00:40:18.170
the bees fly without purpose.

575
00:40:20.280 --> 00:40:23.270
Begging your pardon

576
00:40:20.280 --> 00:40:23.270
for the turn of phrase. Your Grace.

577
00:40:25.220 --> 00:40:27.550
I assume this task

578
00:40:25.220 --> 00:40:27.550
falls within your expertise.

579
00:40:28.720 --> 00:40:29.750
If you wish it.

580
00:40:32.130 --> 00:40:33.120
it will be done.

581
00:41:52.540 --> 00:41:53.700
Out of my way!

582
00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:03.950
With me. Princess.

583
00:42:04.020 --> 00:42:05.880
I cannot let this treachery stand.

584
00:42:46.330 --> 00:42:47.190
Where are we?

585
00:42:48.190 --> 00:42:49.420
Just south of King's Way.

586
00:42:50.500 --> 00:42:51.690
The Blackwater's this way.

587
00:43:20.630 --> 00:43:21.890
I won't leave Meleys.

588
00:43:23.230 --> 00:43:25.260
- If I could get to the Dragonpit. then--

589
00:43:23.230 --> 00:43:25.260
No.

590
00:43:25.360 --> 00:43:27.060
They'll expect you there. Princess.

591
00:43:27.130 --> 00:43:28.360
You won't get past the gates.

592
00:43:29.940 --> 00:43:31.230
Now come.

593
00:43:31.300 --> 00:43:33.470
You must make for the riverfront

594
00:43:31.300 --> 00:43:33.470
and find a ship.

595
00:43:33.570 --> 00:43:35.200
Before they know you've gone.

596
00:43:35.270 --> 00:43:36.940
Move it! Go! Go!

597
00:43:38.040 --> 00:43:39.140
This way!

598
00:43:39.250 --> 00:43:40.440
Keep moving!

599
00:43:41.050 --> 00:43:42.710
That's right. That's right!

600
00:43:45.150 --> 00:43:47.050
Onward!

601
00:43:45.150 --> 00:43:47.050
- This way.

602
00:43:47.120 --> 00:43:48.650
Halt! Halt!

603
00:43:51.660 --> 00:43:53.130
Keep moving!

604
00:43:58.500 --> 00:44:00.470
All of you. move forward!

605
00:44:05.770 --> 00:44:06.900
Keep moving!

606
00:44:17.950 --> 00:44:19.110
Out of the way!

607
00:44:20.790 --> 00:44:21.620
Out of the way!

608
00:44:43.340 --> 00:44:44.970
Have the decency

609
00:44:43.340 --> 00:44:44.970
to look grateful.

610
00:44:46.680 --> 00:44:48.770
Do you know what has been

611
00:44:46.680 --> 00:44:48.770
done to give you this day?

612
00:44:52.620 --> 00:44:54.380
In an hour. you will be king.

613
00:44:54.490 --> 00:44:56.010
And my father never wanted this.

614
00:44:56.120 --> 00:44:57.280
That's not true.

615
00:44:57.360 --> 00:45:00.120
He had 20 years to name me heir

616
00:44:57.360 --> 00:45:00.120
and never did.

617
00:45:00.190 --> 00:45:02.890
Steadfastly. he upheld Rhaenyra's claim.

618
00:45:03.000 --> 00:45:04.400
He changed his mind.

619
00:45:04.500 --> 00:45:06.520
Oh.

620
00:45:07.700 --> 00:45:08.630
No.

621
00:45:09.300 --> 00:45:10.860
He could have. but he never did

622
00:45:12.470 --> 00:45:13.840
because he didn't like me.

623
00:45:15.170 --> 00:45:17.470
And yet. with his final breath.

624
00:45:17.540 --> 00:45:20.640
he whispered to me that you

625
00:45:17.540 --> 00:45:20.640
should take his place on the throne.

626
00:45:41.070 --> 00:45:42.560
Do not toy with me. Mother.

627
00:45:42.670 --> 00:45:43.830
I speak the truth.

628
00:45:58.880 --> 00:46:00.080
Listen to me. Aegon.

629
00:46:01.350 --> 00:46:03.520
Your grandfather. the Hand.

630
00:46:01.350 --> 00:46:03.520
will try to impress on you

631
00:46:03.590 --> 00:46:05.460
that Rhaenyra

632
00:46:03.590 --> 00:46:05.460
should be put to the sword.

633
00:46:05.560 --> 00:46:07.750
You must reject this counsel.

634
00:46:08.760 --> 00:46:10.630
We must not rule

635
00:46:08.760 --> 00:46:10.630
with cruelty and callousness.

636
00:46:10.730 --> 00:46:13.630
For all her faults. she is your sister.

637
00:46:10.730 --> 00:46:13.630
your father's daughter--

638
00:46:13.730 --> 00:46:14.700
Do you love me?

639
00:46:18.640 --> 00:46:19.610
You imbecile.

640
00:46:20.410 --> 00:46:22.410
Make way

641
00:46:20.410 --> 00:46:22.410
for the royal wheelhouse!

642
00:46:39.160 --> 00:46:40.560
Hey. hey. forward then.

643
00:46:43.100 --> 00:46:45.220
Go on. move yourself! Come on!

644
00:47:46.960 --> 00:47:48.480
People of King's Landing.

645
00:47:49.630 --> 00:47:51.650
today is the saddest of days.

646
00:47:53.330 --> 00:47:55.030
Our beloved king.

647
00:47:56.170 --> 00:47:57.970
Viserys the Peaceful.

648
00:48:00.070 --> 00:48:01.040
is dead.

649
00:48:07.750 --> 00:48:10.680
But it is also

650
00:48:07.750 --> 00:48:10.680
the most joyous of days.

651
00:48:12.650 --> 00:48:14.810
For as his spirit left us

652
00:48:17.190 --> 00:48:19.420
he whispered his final wish

653
00:48:19.530 --> 00:48:23.520
that his firstborn son. Aegon.

654
00:48:25.230 --> 00:48:26.820
should succeed him.

655
00:48:38.080 --> 00:48:39.100
Guards!

656
00:48:41.210 --> 00:48:43.410
Out of the way! Move!

657
00:48:51.960 --> 00:48:53.080
Halt!

658
00:48:53.190 --> 00:48:54.130
Turn!

659
00:49:03.770 --> 00:49:04.740
Present...

660
00:49:05.810 --> 00:49:06.900
arms!

661
00:49:40.470 --> 00:49:42.640
It is your great good fortune

662
00:49:42.740 --> 00:49:46.440
and privilege to be here

663
00:49:42.740 --> 00:49:46.440
to witness this.

664
00:49:48.010 --> 00:49:50.510
A new day for our city.

665
00:49:51.580 --> 00:49:53.610
A new day for our realm.

666
00:49:54.190 --> 00:49:58.180
A new king to lead us.

667
00:50:57.150 --> 00:50:59.480
May the Warrior

668
00:50:57.150 --> 00:50:59.480
give him courage.

669
00:51:02.860 --> 00:51:07.020
May the Smith

670
00:51:02.860 --> 00:51:07.020
lend strength to his sword and shield.

671
00:51:09.600 --> 00:51:12.430
May the Father defend him in his need.

672
00:51:15.900 --> 00:51:22.500
May the Crone lift her shining lamp

673
00:51:15.900 --> 00:51:22.500
and light his way to wisdom.

674
00:51:47.700 --> 00:51:50.760
The crown of the Conqueror.

675
00:51:47.700 --> 00:51:50.760
passed down through generations.

676
00:52:09.220 --> 00:52:10.990
Let the Seven bear witness.

677
00:52:11.720 --> 00:52:15.390
Aegon Targaryen

678
00:52:11.720 --> 00:52:15.390
is the true heir to the Iron Throne.

679
00:52:50.360 --> 00:52:54.320
All hail His Grace. Aegon.

680
00:52:55.370 --> 00:52:56.960
Second of his Name.

681
00:52:57.040 --> 00:53:00.770
King of the Andals and the Rhoynar

682
00:52:57.040 --> 00:53:00.770
and the First Men.

683
00:53:00.840 --> 00:53:03.040
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms

684
00:53:03.140 --> 00:53:05.610
and Protector of the Realm.

685
00:53:09.110 --> 00:53:10.380
Aegon the King!

686
00:54:12.880 --> 00:54:14.210
Aegon the King!

687
00:54:14.280 --> 00:54:16.080
Long live Aegon!

688
00:55:18.340 --> 00:55:20.610
Open the doors!

689
00:55:27.920 --> 00:55:28.980
Open the doors!

690
00:55:34.860 --> 00:55:36.020
Get Helaena.
